result.execSummary:
Cindy Jo Libby was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Cindy Jo Libby was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
APPEARANCES:  Defendant Cindy Jo Libby in court, in custody.   Bruce Poquette appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defendant advised of rights/penalties, acknowledges receipt of complaint, and waives right to contact counsel.  

State advises that DE has signed a waiver agreeing to go back to MN already, he requested this hearing so DE would be advised of her rights.  DA will refrain from charging Disorderly Conduct if DE goes back to MN.

DE waives extradition proceedings.
